usecMIB.description: The MIB module for SNMPv2 entities implementing the user- based security model.

AgentID.name: AgentID
AgentID.description: An agent's administratively-unique identifier. The value for this object may not be all zeros or all 'ff'H. The initial value for this object may be configured via an operator console entry or via an algorithmic function. In the later case, the following guidelines are recommended: 1) The first four octets are set to the binary equivalent of the agent's SNMP network management private enterprise number as assigned by the Internet Assigned Numbers Authority (IANA). For example, if Acme Networks has been assigned { enterprises 696 }, the first four octets would be assigned '000002b8'H. 2) The remaining eight octets are the cookie whose contents are determined via one or more enterprise- specific methods. Such methods must be designed so as to maximize the possibility that the value of this object will be unique in the agent's administrative domain. For example, the cookie may be the IP address of the agent, or the MAC address of one of the interfaces, with each address suitably padded with random octets. If multiple methods are defined, then it is recommended that the cookie be further divided into one octet that indicates the method being used and seven octets which are a function of the method.

agentBoots.name: agentBoots
agentBoots.description: The number of times that the agent has re-initialized itself since its initial configuration.

agentTime.name: agentTime
agentTime.description: The number of seconds since the agent last incremented the agentBoots object.

agentSize.name: agentSize
agentSize.description: The maximum length in octets of an SNMPv2 message which this agent will accept using any transport mapping.

usecStatsUnsupportedQoS.name: usecStatsUnsupportedQoS
usecStatsUnsupportedQoS.description: The total number of packets received by the SNMPv2 entity which were dropped because they requested a quality-of- service that was unknown to the agent or otherwise unavailable.

usecStatsNotInWindows.name: usecStatsNotInWindows
usecStatsNotInWindows.description: The total number of packets received by the SNMPv2 entity which were dropped because they appeared outside of the agent's window.

usecStatsUnknownUserNames.name: usecStatsUnknownUserNames
usecStatsUnknownUserNames.description: The total number of packets received by the SNMPv2 entity which were dropped because they referenced a user that was not known to the agent.

usecStatsWrongDigestValues.name: usecStatsWrongDigestValues
usecStatsWrongDigestValues.description: The total number of packets received by the SNMPv2 entity which were dropped because they didn't contain the expected digest value.

usecStatsUnknownContexts.name: usecStatsUnknownContexts
usecStatsUnknownContexts.description: The total number of packets received by the SNMPv2 entity which were dropped because they referenced a context that was not known to the agent.

usecStatsBadParameters.name: usecStatsBadParameters
usecStatsBadParameters.description: The total number of packets received by the SNMPv2 entity which were dropped because the <parameters> field was improperly encoded or had invalid syntax.

usecStatsUnauthorizedOperations.name: usecStatsUnauthorizedOperations
usecStatsUnauthorizedOperations.description: The total number of packets received by the SNMPv2 entity which were dropped because the PDU type referred to an operation that is invalid or not authorized.

usecMIBCompliance.name: usecMIBCompliance
usecMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for SNMPv2 entities which implement the SNMPv2 USEC model.

usecBasicGroup.name: usecBasicGroup
usecBasicGroup.description: A collection of objects providing identification, clocks, and capabilities of an SNMPv2 entity which implements the SNMPv2 USEC model.

usecStatsGroup.name: usecStatsGroup
usecStatsGroup.description: A collection of objects providing basic error statistics of an SNMPv2 entity which implements the SNMPv2 USEC model.
